The paper deals with face alignment and recognition using convolutional neural networks, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The use of neural networks for regression and alignment also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its method on face recognition benchmarks, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) categories.
